Revision history for App-Baphomet

0.0.1	2026-07-12
        - Initial release. Log watcher for Ereshkigal... tails logs, parses
          syslog lines, matches them against YAML rules, and consigns
          offending IPs to Kur via the Ereshkigal manager socket.
        - A watcher's log may be a array of files and entries may be
          globs, re-expanded every ten seconds while running, so new
          matches, like a freshly created jail, get picked up live.
        - The raw parser is the no-op escape hatch, the whole line as the
          message, matched by rules of the raw type... syslog rules minus
          the daemon gate. Never format-sniffed, only explicitly
          configured. Ships raw/mysqld-auth, raw/exim, and raw/3proxy.
        - The apache_error and nginx_error parsers handle the web server
          error logs, matched by rules of the http_error type... level and
          module gates plus message regexps, banning the parsed client.
          nginx structured pairs are peeled into fields, rightmost wins
          against injection. Rules may set test_parser to default the
          parser for all their embedded tests.
        - The http_access parser handles common and combined HTTP access
          logs, matched by rules of the new http type... gates on status
          and method plus per-field match/ignore regexps, banning the
          client field. Ships http/badbots and http/botsearch. Rule types
          and parsers are cross-checked at start.
        - The syslog parser handles RFC 3164, RFC 5424, and the JSON
          output of syslog-ng (also available on its own as json_syslog),
          sniffed per line, and is the default when a watcher does not
          name a parser. Parsed lines carry a format key saying which
          won. The syslog rules apply to JSON logs unchanged.
        - Rules may carry ignore_regexp entries, the fail2ban ignoreregex
          equivalent, and a watcher's rule may be a array of rules checked
          first-match-wins, for logs carrying several daemons.
        - Licensed GPL-2.0-or-later, matching fail2ban, which the shipped
          rules are derived from.
        - Ships 25 syslog rules translated from the fail2ban filters, each
          carrying tests mined from the fail2ban test log corpus. See
          docs/rules-catalog.md.
